9602 ScalarEvolution::getMonotonicPredicateTypeImpl(const SCEVAddRecExpr *LHS,
9603                                                ICmpInst::Predicate Pred) {
9604   // A zero step value for LHS means the induction variable is essentially a
9605   // loop invariant value. We don't really depend on the predicate actually
9606   // flipping from false to true (for increasing predicates, and the other way
9607   // around for decreasing predicates), all we care about is that *if* the
9608   // predicate changes then it only changes from false to true.
9609   //
9610   // A zero step value in itself is not very useful, but there may be places
9611   // where SCEV can prove X >= 0 but not prove X > 0, so it is helpful to be
